	<h1>12 Ways to Maximize Financial Aid</h1>
	
	<p>First, a little math: for every $10,000 of financial aid you receive each year, that's $10,000 saved. But remember, you pay the college with dollars that have already been taxed (say, 23% federal, 2.8% state, and 7.65% FICA and Medicare). In other words, $10,000 of aid is equivalent to over $15,000 of earnings.</p>
	
